===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|fr|(dialectal) [[beige]]}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|bege||color of undyed wool or cotton}}, from an Alpine language (compare Franco-Provençal {{m|frp|bézho}}, Romansch {{m|rm|besch||dull grey}}), from {{etyl|VL.|en}} {{m|la|*bysseus||cottony grey}} (compare French {{m|fr|bis}}, Catalan {{m|ca|bis}}, Italian {{m|it|bigio|bìgio}}), from {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{m|la|byssus}} 'cotton', from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|βύσσος|}} 'cotton homespun', from Semitic (compare {{etyl|he|en}}/{{etyl|arc|en}} {{m|he|בוץ||tr=būṣ}})

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|[beɪʒ]|[beɪdʒ]|lang=en}}
